The spiral is the usual “Ulam” spiral:

```
... 5 4 3 ...
... 6 1 2 ...
... 7 8 9 ...
```

Let the centre 1 be at \((0,0)\).  
For a point \((x,y)\) set  

\[
k=\max(|x|,|y|) .
\]

The largest number on the square of radius \(k\) is  

\[
M_k=(2k+1)^2
\]

which sits at \((k,-k)\).  
Going clockwise from that corner the offsets are  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{bottom edge}&: y=-k,\;x\in[k,\dots,-k] &
\displaystyle\text{offset}=k-x\\[4pt]
\text{left edge}&: x=-k,\;y\in[-k+1,\dots ,k] &
\displaystyle\text{offset}=2k+(y+k)\\[4pt]
\text{top edge}&: y=k,\;x\in[-k+1,\dots ,k] &
\displaystyle\text{offset}=4k+(x+k)\\[4pt]
\text{right edge}&: x=k,\;y\in[k-1,\dots ,-k] &
\displaystyle\text{offset}=6k+(k-y)
\end{aligned}
\]

The number at \((x,y)\) is then  

\[
N(x,y)=M_k-\text{offset}.
\]

---

### 1.  Locate 2026  

\(2026\) lies in the ring with  

\[
k=\min\{k\mid (2k+1)^2\ge2026\}=23,\qquad M_{23}=47^2=2209 .
\]

The offset of 2026 from the maximum of this ring is  

\[
2209-2026=183 .
\]

Since the perimeter of a ring is \(8k=184\), the offset \(183\) lands on the **right edge**, \(45\) steps down from the top‑right corner.  
Hence  

\[
(2026)=(23,-22).
\]

---

### 2.  The eight neighbours  

\[
\begin{array}{c|c|c}
\text{Neighbour}&\text{Coordinates}&\text{Number}\\ \hline
(22,-23) & (22,-23) & 2208\\
(23,-23) & (23,-23) & 2209\\
(24,-23) & (24,-23) & 2210\\
(22,-22) & (22,-22) & 2025\\
(24,-22) & (24,-22) & 2211\\
(22,-21) & (22,-21) & 1850\\
(23,-21) & (23,-21) & 2027\\
(24,-21) & (24,-21) & 2212
\end{array}
\]

(For the points with \(|x|\,\)or \(|y|=24\) we use the same formulas with \(k=24\).)

---

### 3.  Sum of the neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\sum &= 2208+2209+2210+2211+2212 \\
     &\quad +2025+2027+1850 \\[2pt]
     &= 5\cdot2210 + (2025+2027) + 1850 \\[2pt]
     &= 11050 + 4052 + 1850 \\[2pt]
     &= 16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
